2 NOTE Boy 1st Class. 
3 CONT On 17 October 1903, Prince George was badly damaged when her sister ship Hannibal rammed her in heavy seas at a speed of 9 knots (17 km/h; 10 mph) off Spain, punching a large hole below the waterline on Prince George's starboard quarter.
1 DSCR Height 5'5", Brown hair, hazel eyes, fresh complexion.  Tattoos; "I love JC" on right forearm, anchor on left forearm, 5 dots and ring on left hand.
