2 TITL Cathedral and the Old  Deanery Rochester
1 _OID 0c6c6a5b-078c-4a8b-9d85-172aeea7da6f
1 PLAC Rochester, Kent, England
1 _DSCR This phot shows the old Deanery Buildings infront of Rochester cathedral.  Rochester is the town that was just across the river from Frindsbury.  These building would have been there when William and Elizabeth Hammond and their children lived in th
2 CONC e area.  It is great to think our ancestors would have look upon these building and maybe have entered them as part of their life in The Rochester area.
