2 TITL HMS Parthian from wikipedia
1 _OID 3712ac91-eda9-4af9-b965-e7ffdf98360d
1 _META <metadataxml><content><line>&lt;p&gt;&lt;font color="#000000"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;HMS &lt;em&gt;Parthian&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;, pennant number (N75) was the &lt;/font&gt;&lt;font color="#000000"&gt;lead boat&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font color="#000000"&gt
2 CONC ; of the 6 &lt;/font&gt;&lt;font color="#000000"&gt;Parthian class submarines&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font color="#000000"&gt; all launched in 1929. The &lt;/font&gt;&lt;font color="#000000"&gt;Royal Navy&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font color="#000000"&gt; submarin
2 CONC e was sunk in 1943 during the &lt;/font&gt;&lt;font color="#000000"&gt;Second World War&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font color="#000000"&gt;. The submarine was nicknamed &lt;/font&gt;&lt;font color="#000000"&gt;Peanut&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font color="#000000"&gt;
2 CONC , from the identity letters PN painted on the &lt;/font&gt;&lt;font color="#000000"&gt;fin&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font color="#000000"&gt;.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font color="#000000"&gt;&lt;em&gt;Parthian&lt;/em&gt; spent most of her Second W
2 CONC orld War service in the Mediterranean. On the outbreak of the Second World War, she was stationed with the China Fleet, but was transferred to &lt;/font&gt;&lt;font color="#000000"&gt;Alexandria&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font color="#000000"&gt; in May 1940
2 CONC . She sunk the Italian submarine &lt;em&gt;Diamante&lt;/em&gt; near &lt;/font&gt;&lt;font color="#000000"&gt;Tobruk&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font color="#000000"&gt; on &lt;/font&gt;&lt;font color="#000000"&gt;20 June&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font color="#000000"&gt
2 CONC ; &lt;/font&gt;&lt;font color="#000000"&gt;1940&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font color="#000000"&gt;. By the end of the year she had been attached to the 8th Submarine Flotilla based at &lt;/font&gt;&lt;font color="#000000"&gt;Malta&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font color=
2 CONC "#000000"&gt;.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font color="#000000"&gt;It also sank the &lt;/font&gt;&lt;font color="#000000"&gt;Vichy French&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font color="#000000"&gt; submarine &lt;em&gt;Souffleur&lt;/em&gt; off Beirut on &lt;/fo
2 CONC nt&gt;&lt;font color="#000000"&gt;25 June&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font color="#000000"&gt; 1941, during the combined British/&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font color="#000000"&gt;Free French&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font color="#000000"&gt; campaign to occupy &lt;/font&gt;&lt;f
2 CONC ont color="#000000"&gt;Syria&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font color="#000000"&gt; and &lt;/font&gt;&lt;font color="#000000"&gt;Lebanon&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font color="#000000"&gt;. &lt;em&gt;Parthian&lt;/em&gt; underwent a refit in the USA from late 1941 until Mar
2 CONC ch 1942 before returning to the Mediterranean, where she carried out supply operations between July and October to &lt;/font&gt;&lt;font color="#000000"&gt;Malta&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font color="#000000"&gt; carrying &lt;/font&gt;&lt;font color="#000000
2 CONC "&gt;aviation fuel&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font color="#000000"&gt; and &lt;/font&gt;&lt;font color="#000000"&gt;ammunition&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font color="#000000"&gt;. To increase her cargo capacity, one of the batteries was removed and no reload torpedoes c
2 CONC arried. In May 1043 the submarine sank a number of Italian sailing vessels in the &lt;/font&gt;&lt;font color="#000000"&gt;Aegean Sea&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font color="#000000"&gt;.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font color="#000000"&gt;The submarin
2 CONC e left Malta on &lt;/font&gt;&lt;font color="#000000"&gt;22 July&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font color="#000000"&gt; 1943 for a patrol in the southern Adriatic. She was diverted to a patrol area off &lt;/font&gt;&lt;font color="#000000"&gt;Otranto&lt;/font&gt
2 CONC ;&lt;font color="#000000"&gt; on 26 July, and diverted again on 28 July. The submarine was signalled on &lt;/font&gt;&lt;font color="#000000"&gt;6 August&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font color="#000000"&gt; leave the patrol area but the signal was not acknowle
2 CONC dged. &lt;em&gt;Parthian&lt;/em&gt; failed to arrive at &lt;/font&gt;&lt;font color="#000000"&gt;Beirut&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font color="#000000"&gt;, where she was due on &lt;/font&gt;&lt;font color="#000000"&gt;11 August&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font color="#0
2 CONC 00000"&gt;. It is likely that she was sunk by a &lt;/font&gt;&lt;font color="#000000"&gt;naval mine&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font color="#000000"&gt; near Brindisi.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</line></content></metadataxml>
