2 TITL Minster Church, and the old dockyard area of Sheerness.
1 _OID 3e59952e-4480-42ba-b658-1b51334fde04
1 PLAC Minster and Sheerness, Isle of Sheppey,Kent.
1 _DSCR These pictures give an idea of the isle of Sheppey that William would have known as a child.  At least two generations of Hammond's before William lived on the island, and many more relations married islanders.  Their lives revolved around the dock
2 CONC s.  William and Elizabeth's son Thomas b1772 married Mary Mitchell and moved onto the Island and brought up their children there, and so more generations carried on dwelling in Sheerness and Minster and Eastchurch.
