2 TITL Frindsbury 1770
1 _OID 43f51094-c387-46e1-944f-126984e7cf19
1 DATE 1770
1 PLAC A view near Frindsbury, Rochester, Kent, England
1 _DSCR This painting gives us an idea of the rural setting on 18th century Frindsbury.  William and Elizabeth Hammond were bringing up their young family and would have crossed the brighe and walked along the roads and fields.  It's nice to have a contemp
2 CONC ory snap shot of the place our ancestors lived in, it may be a romantised painting, but it gives us an idea what was there at the time.
