2 TITL HMS Parthian History
1 _OID 71badbc3-5143-4cf6-b0f7-f74f7a5c5c86
1 DATE 1940-1943
1 _META <metadataxml><content><line>HMS Parthian was refitted in U.S.A. from late 1941 until March 1942. After this refit she went back to the Mediterranean and was used for supply runs to Malta. In May 1943 HMS Parthian (Lt. M.B. St. John, RN) sank severa
2 CONC l Italian sailing vessels while operating in the Aegean. &lt;p&gt;HMS Parthian (Lt. &lt;em&gt;Cyril Astell&lt;/em&gt; Pardoe, RNR) is presumed mined in Adriatic late July / early August 1943. Having sailed from Malta on 22nd July for patrol west o
2 CONC f Greece in the southern Adriatic. She was ordered to patrol off Otranto on 26th July 1943. She was again given a new area to patrol on the 28th. She was reported overdue at Beirut on 11th August 1943. Most likely she was mined off Brindisi. The da
2 CONC te given as lost (11 August 1943) is the date she was reported missing.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Noteable events involving Parthian include:&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;17 Jun, 1940&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;HMS Parthian (L
2 CONC t.Cdr. M.G. Rimington, RN) attacks the Italian destroyer &lt;strong&gt;Nembo&lt;/strong&gt; with torpedoes off Tobruk, Libya. However all torpedoes fired missed their target.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;19 Jun, 1940&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;HM
2 CONC S Parthian (Lt.Cdr. M.G. Rimington, RN) fires two torpedoes at the old Italian armoured cruiser &lt;strong&gt;San Giorgio&lt;/strong&gt; off Tobruk. The torpedoes however got stuck in the net defences and/or mud.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;2
2 CONC 0 Jun, 1940&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;HMS Parthian (Lt.Cdr. M.G. Rimington, RN) torpedoes and sinks the Italian submarine &lt;strong&gt;Diamante&lt;/strong&gt; about 35 nautical miles north-north-west of Tobruk, Libya in position 32&amp;ordm;42&amp;#
2 CONC 39;N, 23&amp;ordm;49&amp;#39;E (see map)&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;20 Jul, 1940&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;HMS Parthian (Lt.Cdr. M.G. Rimington, RN) landed an agent on Crete.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;31 Aug, 1940&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;H
2 CONC MS Parthian (Lt.Cdr. M.G. Rimington, RN) attacks the Italian cruisers &lt;strong&gt;Giuseppe Garibaldi&lt;/strong&gt; and &lt;strong&gt;Luigi di Savoia Duca Delgi Abruzzi&lt;/strong&gt; in the Ionian Sea about 105 nautical miles east-south-east o
2 CONC f Cape Spartivento, Italy in position 37&amp;ordm;45&amp;#39;N, 18&amp;ordm;22&amp;#39;E. All torpedoes fired missed their target. (see map)&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;9 Jan, 1941&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;HMS Parthian (Lt.Cdr. M.G. Rimington, D
2 CONC SO, RN) torpedoes and sinks the Italian merchant &lt;strong&gt;Carlo Martinolich&lt;/strong&gt; (4208 GRT) about 10 nautical miles east of Punta Stilo, Calabria, Italy in position 38&amp;ordm;28&amp;#39;N, 16&amp;ordm;44&amp;#39;E. (see map)&lt;/p&
2 CONC gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;16 Mar, 1941&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;HMS Parthian (Lt.Cdr. M.G. Rimington, DSO, RN) torpedoes and damages the Iitalian merchant &lt;strong&gt;Giovanni Bocaccio&lt;/strong&gt; (3141 GRT) in the central Mediterranean about 5
2 CONC 5 nautical miles east of Malta in position 35&amp;ordm;57&amp;#39;N, 15&amp;ordm;40&amp;#39;E. (see map)&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;3 Jun, 1941&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;HMS Parthian (Cdr. M.G. Rimington, DSO, RN) torpedoes and damages the Itali
2 CONC an oiler &lt;strong&gt;Strombo&lt;/strong&gt; (5232 GRT) east of Limnos in position 39&amp;ordm;57&amp;#39;N, 25&amp;ordm;38&amp;#39;E. (see map)&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;8 Jun, 1941&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;HMS Parthian (Cdr. M.G. Rimington
2 CONC , DSO, RN) sinks 2 sailing vessels and an other small vessel at Mitylene, Lesbos, Greece. Parthian fired two torpedoes in the harbour. &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;25 Jun, 1941&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;HMS Parthian (Cdr. M.G. Rimington, DSO, RN
2 CONC ) torpedoes and sinks the Vichy French submarine &lt;strong&gt;Souffleur&lt;/strong&gt; south-west of Beirut in position 33&amp;ordm;49&amp;#39;N, 35&amp;ordm;26&amp;#39;E. (see map)&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;16 Nov, 1942&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br
2 CONC &gt;At 1048 hours HMS Parthian (Lt. M.B. St. John, RN) fires four torpedoes against a convoy made up of the small Italian tanker &lt;strong&gt;Labor&lt;/strong&gt; (510 GRT), the German merchant &lt;strong&gt;Menes&lt;/strong&gt; (5609 GRT) escorte
2 CONC d by the Italian torpedo boats &lt;strong&gt;Calliope&lt;/strong&gt; and &lt;strong&gt;Climene&lt;/strong&gt; north-east of Isola Marettimo, Italy in position 38&amp;ordm;03&amp;#39;N, 11&amp;ordm;51&amp;#39;E. All torpedoes fired missed their targ
2 CONC et(s). (see map)&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;28 Mar, 1943&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;HMS Parthian (Lt. M.B. St. John, RN) sinks the Greek sailing vessel &lt;strong&gt;Archangelos&lt;/strong&gt; (120 GRT) with gunfire and ramming in the Aegean Se
2 CONC a west of Lesbos Island, Greece in position 39&amp;ordm;19&amp;#39;N, 25&amp;ordm;18&amp;#39;E.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;29 Mar, 1943&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;HMS Parthian (Lt. M.B. St. John, RN) sinks the Greek sailing vessel &lt;strong&gt;A
2 CONC ngela Mitylene&lt;/strong&gt; (120 GRT) off Mitylene, Greece.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;4 May, 1943&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;HMS Parthian (Lt. M.B. St. John, RN) sinks the Italian sailing vessels &lt;strong&gt;Despina II&lt;/strong&gt; and &lt
2 CONC ;strong&gt;Spina Secundo&lt;/strong&gt; (both 13 GRT) with gunfire off Kos, Greece.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;5 May, 1943&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;HMS Parthian (Lt. M.B. St. John, RN) attacks the German auxiliary minelayer &lt;strong&gt;Drache
2 CONC &lt;/strong&gt; with gunfire about 7 nautical miles north-east of Doro in position 38&amp;ordm;20&amp;#39;N, 24&amp;ordm;46&amp;#39;E. (see map)&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;7 May, 1943&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;HMS Parthian (Lt. M.B. St. John, RN
2 CONC ) sinks the Italian sailing vessel &lt;strong&gt;Barbara&lt;/strong&gt; about 10 nautical miles north of Cape Stavros, Naxos, Greece&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;25 Jun, 1943&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;HMS Parthian (Lt. M.B. St. John, RN) attacks t
2 CONC he German merchant &lt;strong&gt;Gerda Toft&lt;/strong&gt; (1960 GRT) in the Aegean Sea off Cape Midia. Possibly there was one dud torpedo hit.&lt;/p&gt;</line></content></metadataxml>
