1 _OID 7d52ca09-fd89-4741-8c1e-399a8ca11f63
1 _META <metadataxml><content><line>&lt;span style="font-family: times; font-size: 16px"&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;font face="Arial, Helvetica"&gt;&lt;p style="text-align: " align="center"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: 'times new roman mt extra bold'"&gt;&lt;spa
2 CONC n style="font-size: small"&gt;Thomas Ithill (Ethell) was born as William Smith, on the 3rd August 1759 at Prees,Shropshire, the illegitimate son of Ann Smith, the father being Francis Reynolds, a married man.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;
2 CONC p style="text-align: " align="center"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: 'times new roman mt extra bold'"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: 'times new roman mt extra bold'"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: small"&gt;Between 1756 and 1760, The Foundling Hos
2 CONC pital, London, and other similar places in England were obliged to accept all children offered to it and many Parishes throughout England saw this as a way of disposing of illegitimate children who were a charge on the parish.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span
2 CONC &gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style="text-align: " align="center"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: 'times new roman mt extra bold'"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: 'times new roman mt extra bold'"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: small"&gt;Thomas It
2 CONC hill (William Smith) was one of these children who were placed in the Foundling Hospital and given a new name. From the Foundling Hospital Register, on the 4th September 1759 a male child about one month old requiring a wet nurse was admitted bein
2 CONC g given number 13853, the child was born in Prees Parish,Shropshire, 3rd August 1759, No 13853 named Thomas Ithill.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style="text-align: " align="center"&gt;&lt;font face="Times New Roman MT Extr
2 CONC a Bold"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: small"&gt;After nine years at the Foundling Hospital, Thomas was sent to Ackworth Hospital,near Pontefract,Yorkshire. Two years later on the 9th June 1768 he was apprenticed to John Frear of Norton,near Malton,
2 CONC Yorkshire,a Farmer, to be employed in Husbandry.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style="text-align: " align="center"&gt;&lt;font face="Times New Roman MT Extra Bold"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: small"&gt;Thomas Ithill (Ethell) married De
2 CONC borah Rose in Scampston Chapel,near Rillington,Yorkshire, on the 12th February 1782, they had three children&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style="text-align: " align="center"&gt;&lt;font face="Times New Roman MT Extra Bold"&gt;
2 CONC &lt;span style="font-size: small"&gt;John. born 1782&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style="text-align: " align="center"&gt;&lt;font face="Times New Roman MT Extra Bold"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: small"&gt;Richard. born 1784&lt;/span&g
2 CONC t;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style="text-align: " align="center"&gt;&lt;font face="Times New Roman MT Extra Bold"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: small"&gt;Hannah. born 1790.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style="text-align: " align="cent
2 CONC er"&gt;&lt;font face="Times New Roman MT Extra Bold"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: arial"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: small"&gt;When Thomas died at the age of 83 years he had 24 grandchildren.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt
2 CONC ;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/span&gt;</line></content></metadataxml>
