2 TITL William Hammond of Frindsbury, (1737-1788), Overseerer of the Poor.
1 _OID 813015f1-619e-4e33-9752-ac0b2fd3a226
1 DATE 1777
1 PLAC Frindsbury parish chest document, Overseers of the poor.
1 _DSCR This photo was taken at The Centre for Kentish Studies Archives, Strood, Kent.
2 CONT 
2 CONT This page shows the payments that William Hammond had to pay out to parishioners of the parish who were paid for providing a service to the comunity, such as looking after a sick person etc. or providing something needed in the church its self, a
2 CONC s William himself was paid for books,  (perhaps new register books or note books for vestry meetings, or some sort of printed mater), from William's shop.
