2 CONC ce="Times New Roman" size="3"&gt;  &lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font size="3"&gt;&lt;font face="Times New Roman"&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span&gt;Cross-examined.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;span&gt; He said &amp;quot;preying,&amp;quot; not &amp;quot;playing.&a
2 CONC mp;quot;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font face="Times New Roman" size="3"&gt;  &lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font size="3"&gt;&lt;font face="Times New Roman"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;HENRY GOULD &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;s
2 CONC pan&gt;, M.R.C.S., and Divisional Surgeon of Police. I reside at Leyton&amp;mdash;about 6 o&amp;#39;clock on the evening of the 8th I was called by Inspector Folkard, and went with him to 8, Courtney Place, and into the front room on the first floo
2 CONC r&amp;mdash;I there saw a bed in which were two male children, apparently a few days old&amp;mdash;I examined them, and found them both suffering from fractured skulls; blood was issuing from the nose and mouth of one of them&amp;mdash;they were li
2 CONC ving, but in a dying state&amp;mdash;I then went into the kitchen and saw three children lying on their faces on the floor, dead&amp;mdash;the clothes of two that had clothes on were saturated with water&amp;mdash;on the eldest, Charles, there wa
2 CONC s a mark as if a piece of thin string had been tied round his throat&amp;mdash;the others had no marks whatever&amp;mdash;the same night, shortly after 8, I went to the house, and found there that one of the younger children had died, and next morn
2 CONC ing I found the other of the twins dead&amp;mdash;I made a post-mortem examination on the 9th of all the bodies&amp;mdash;the two younger died from injury to the skull and brain; the three in the kitchen died from suffocation from drowning&amp;mdas
2 CONC h;before this injury they were apparently in health and fairly nourished.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;font face="Times New Roman" size="3"&gt;  &lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font size="3"&gt;&lt;font face="Times New Roman"&gt;&l
