2 TITL Hannah Ethell&#39;s unborn child
1 _OID d5511ea9-b50a-4589-a74d-e8b035beedb0
1 _META <metadataxml><content><line>Notes for Hannah Ethell</line><line>&lt;div&gt;</line><line>&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;</line><line>&lt;div&gt;&lt;span id="ul_a03d99c5"&gt;easyuk&lt;/span&gt; added this on 4 Sep 2011&lt;/div&gt;</line><line>&lt;d
2 CONC iv&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;</line><line>&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;</line><line>&lt;/div&gt;</line><line>&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; Bastardy Recognition of James Hudson East Riding Archives, Beverley Session Midsummer 1809 QSU/1/10/15 East Ridin
2 CONC g of Yorkshire Be it remembered that James Hudson of Yedingham [see note below] in the said Riding, Farmer's Servant and William Ruddock of New Malton in the North Riding of Yorkshire, Tradesman the 29th day of April in the Year of Our Lord one tho
2 CONC usand eight hundred and nine came before me John Robinson Francis Esquire one of his Majesty's Justices of the Peace for the said Riding, and in their proper person acknowledged themselves to be indebted to our Sovereign Lord the King, in manner fo
2 CONC llowing, that is to say, the said James Hudson twenty pounds and the said William Ruddock twenty pounds to be made and levied on their land and tenements, gardens and chattels, respectively, to the use of the said Lord the King, his Heirs and Succe
2 CONC ssors if default should be made in the condition following. Whereas Hannah Ethell of Sledmere in the said East Riding single woman, hath, in and by her voluntary examination, taken in writing, on oath, before me one of his Majesty's Justices of th
2 CONC e Peace for the said Riding, declared herself with child, and the said child is likely to be born a Bastard, and to be chargeable to the said township of Sledmere and that the above-bounden James Hudson is the Father of such child. The condition, t
2 CONC herefore, of the above Recognizance is such, That if the said James Hudson do and shall appear personally at the next General Quarter-Sessions of the Peace, to be holden in and for the said Riding, and abide by and perform such order or orders as s
2 CONC hall be made in pursuance of an Act passed in the 18th year of the reign of Queen Elizabeth, concerning Bastards, begotten and born out of lawful matrimony, Recognizance to be void, otherwise of force. Acknowledged before me J. R. Francis [signed]&
2 CONC lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</line></content></metadataxml>
