2 TITL Altar, All Saints, Frindsbury
1 _OID f00b1637-d048-4d94-956a-f28df165a4c4
1 DATE 1766
1 _DSCR This photo shows the interior of All Saints, Frindsbury.  The parish church was the centre of villiage life  (as well as the village tavern).  William and Elizabeth baptised their children here, and sadley attended some of their childrens funeral
2 CONC s as shown on the family Headstone that stands proudly outside the church porchway.  They would have attended all sorts of services, Sunday's, friends and family, baptisms, marriages and funerals, Rogations day when the plough was blessed, Easter a
2 CONC nd Harvest festival, and christmas day, and others I have not mentioned.  It is nice to be able to see where they gathered, chatted, laughed,cried and prayed, and maybe sang.
1 _CREA 2022-01-19 14:39:02.000
